The paper discusses the selection of research products for national research assessment exercises, which involves evaluating the quality of research in institutions. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), computational complexity (cs.CY), information retrieval (cs.IR), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). However, since the paper focuses on the evaluation of research quality, we believe that cs.DL and cs.CY are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.IR, cs.CR, and cs.AI.
